</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Alternating Bicep Curl Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand using a shoulder-width stance, holding a suitable pair of dumbbells by your sides. Use a neutral grip with your palms facing inwards.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Keep your chest up with your head facing forwards.</li>



<li>Flex your elbow, bringing the dumbbell up to chest height. As it comes up to 90 degrees, rotate your hand so you’re using a supinated grip.</li>



<li>Pause briefly at the top position, squeezing your bicep. Exhale and bring the dumbbell back down. Rotate your wrist back to a neutral grip as it comes back past 90 degrees.</li>



<li>Once it reaches the starting position, switch to the other arm. Perform the same movement pattern as stated above.</li>



<li>Alternate between both arms for the stated number of sets and reps.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/decline-dumbbell-tricep-extension" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Decline Dumbbell Tricep Extension</a></h3>



