</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Seated Shoulder Press Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Adjust the bench back pad until it’s at the most upright position. Set a pair of dumbbells on the floor; one on either side of the seat.</li>



<li>Pick the dumbbells up with a neutral back position and sit on the bench.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Use an overhead grip with your palms facing inward. Allow the dumbbells to rest on your knees.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Ensure your feet are firmly on the ground and your back is against the pad. Your head should be facing forward. This is your correct starting position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Take a deep breath in and engage your core. Using your knees, kick the dumbbells up towards your shoulders one at a time.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Adjust your elbows to point sideways at a 45-degree angle.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Press both dumbbells overhead. Extend both elbows until the dumbbells nearly touch. Pause briefly at the top position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Start to bring the dumbbells back down under control. Take a breath out at the same time.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Once they reach shoulder height again, repeat the same movements from step five for the desired repetitions and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/alternating-dumbbell-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Alternating Dumbbell Press</a></h3>



