</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Seated Lateral Raise Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Choose a set of dumbbells that are appropriate for your strength level.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Sit on a flat bench with your feet planted on the ground, slightly wider than shoulder width to provide stability. Adjust the backrest until it’s at a 90-degree angle.</li>



<li>Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms relaxed at your sides and your palms facing your thighs.</li>



<li>Pull your shoulders back and down to ensure they stay in a safe and stable position.</li>



<li>Take a deep breath in and engage your core. Ensure your elbows are by your sides with a slight bend.</li>



<li>Raise the dumbbells out to the sides until your arms are parallel to the floor. Your palms should be facing the ground at the top of the movement.</li>



<li>When your arms are parallel to the ground, hold the position for a second. Ensure you feel the contraction in your shoulder muscles.</li>



<li>Exhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. Keep the movement controlled and maintain the slight bend in your elbows.</li>



<li>Perform the desired number of repetitions, maintaining proper form.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-upright-row" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Dumbbell Upright Row</a></h3>



