<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Let your arms hang straight down with your palms facing your thighs.</li>



<li>Keep your back straight and engage your core. Ensure your head is aligned with your spine.</li>



<li>Inhale, and as you exhale, lift the dumbbells by raising your elbows out to the sides and upward. Keep the dumbbells close to your body.</li>



<li>Continue lifting until the dumbbells reach chest level or just below your chin. Your elbows should be higher than your wrists.</li>



<li>Pause briefly at the top of the movement. Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat the movement for the desired repetitions, maintaining proper form throughout.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-bent-over-rear-delt-fly" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Dumbbell Bent-Over Rear Delt Fly</a></h3>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Dumbbell Bent-Over Rear Delt Fly" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/984816319?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
