<li>Hold one dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip, palms facing each other.</li>



<li>Lean forward while keeping the back flat and core engaged. Your arms should be fully extended with a slight bend in the elbow.</li>



<li>Brace the core and inhale to raise the dumbbells out to the sides of your body. Focus on squeezing the shoulder blades together during the movement. This engages the deltoids and back muscles through the full range of motion.</li>



<li>Hold at the top for a second to maximally engage. Exhale while slowly lowering the arms back down to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of reps and sets.</li>
