<iframe loading="lazy" title="Side Lying Dumbbell Rear Delt Raise" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1011888324?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Side Lying Dumbbell Rear Delt Raise Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Grab one dumbbell.</li>



<li>Locate an available flat bench for the exercise.</li>



<li>Shift the dumbbell to your left hand.</li>



<li>Lay down on your right side on the bench.</li>



<li>Position yourself so that your right arm is over the top of the bench to press down into the ground.</li>



<li>Adjust your left arm in front of you, bending at the elbow.</li>



<li>Hold the dumbbell in an overhand grip, twisting it so your palm faces your feet.</li>



<li>Inhale, lowering the dumbbell to your chest. Ensure the movement comes from your shoulder. Keep your elbow at a fixed angle.</li>



<li>Pause at the bottom.</li>



<li>Exhale, engaging the rear delt to raise the dumbbell above your head.</li>



<li>Repeat for desired reps and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start" id="Back-Dumbbell-Exercises">Back Dumbbell Exercises</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-single-arm-bent-over-row" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Dumbbell Single-Arm Bent-Over Row</a></h3>



