<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand next to a flat weight bench with a dumbbell at the side.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Place your left knee and left hand on the bench, keeping your right foot flat on the ground.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Bend at your hips so your back is flat with your head facing down. Reach down and grab the dumbbell with your right arm extended.</li>



<li>Take a deep breath in and engage your core. Bring your elbow up and back at a 45-degree angle.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Once the dumbbell reaches the hip height, pause briefly to better engage your lat.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Bring the dumbbell back down using the reverse motion. Take a deep breath out as you control the descent.</li>



<li>Perform the required number of repetitions and switch to the other hand.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-bent-over-row" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Dumbbell Bent-Over Row</a></h3>



