<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin with your feet hip-width apart, knees slightly bent. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing together.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Keep your shoulder blades packed down, push your hips back, and maintain a strong bent-over position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Exhale and draw your elbows back, squeezing the shoulder blades back and down to bring the dumbbells towards you.</li>



<li>Pause for a second at the top position. Inhale and fully extend your arms back to the starting position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Maintaining the bent-over position, perform the desired number of repetitions.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-shrug" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Dumbbell Shrug</a></h3>



