</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Renegade Row Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Set up your dumbbells or kettlebells around shoulder-width apart.</li>



<li>Take a plank position with your hands holding onto the weights. You want your feet wider than hip-width apart to help maximize stability.</li>



<li>Position yourself so that your chin is in front of the dumbbells and your shoulders are stacked over your wrists.</li>



<li>Pushing down with your left hand, lift your right hand as you inhale, keeping your arm tucked alongside the body. Aim for the weight to end up in the middle of your torso.</li>



<li>As you lift the weight, ensure your chest remains parallel to the floor. You don’t want much rotation through the trunk.</li>



<li>As you exhale, lower your right arm to the ground and switch sides.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-pullover" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Dumbbell Pullover</a></h3>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Dumbbell Pullover" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/984680529?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Pullover Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Lie flat on a bench with your head near one end and your feet firmly planted on the ground for stability.</li>



<li>Hold a dumbbell with both hands, palms pressed against the inside part of the weight plate, and thumbs wrapped around the handle for a secure grip.</li>



<li>Extend your arms straight above your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. Engage your core and ensure your back remains flat against the bench.</li>



<li>Slowly lower the dumbbell in an arc-like motion over your head, keeping your arms slightly bent. Lower the weight until your arms are in line with your torso or you feel a stretch in your chest and lats.</li>



<li>Inhale deeply as you lower the dumbbell to maintain stability and control.</li>



<li>Exhale as you reverse the motion, bringing the dumbbell back over your chest. Focus on using your chest and lats to lift the weight, maintaining control throughout the movement.</li>



<li>Repeat the exercise for the desired number of repetitions, ensuring proper form and controlled movements.</li>



<li>At the end of your set, carefully bring the dumbbell down to your chest before sitting up to avoid strain. Keep a controlled tempo to maximize muscle engagement and reduce the risk of injury.</li>
</ol>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start" id="Leg-Dumbbell-Exercises">Leg Dumbbell Exercises</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-lunge" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Dumbbell Lunge</a></h3>



