</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Standing Calf Raise Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Start by grabbing a suitable pair of dumbbells and find a raised surface. You can use a step, plate, or plyometric box.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Hold the dumbbells with your palms facing the outside of your thighs and step onto the raised platform.</li>



<li>Make sure the balls of your feet are on the edge with your heels hanging off. This is your starting position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Stand upright with the dumbbells at your sides. Take a deep breath in and engage your core.&nbsp;</li>



<li>With your knees fully extended, press the balls of your feet into the ground. Lift both heels as high as you can while keeping your legs straight.</li>



<li>When you reach the top position, pause briefly and squeeze both calves.</li>



<li>Slowly lower back down to the starting position. At the same time, take a slow breath out.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-romanian-deadlift" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Dumbbell Romanian Deadlift</a></h3>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
