</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Romanian Deadlift Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Start by picking up your dumbbells and holding one in each of your hands. Hold the dumbbells at a 45-degree rotation angle beside your thighs, not right in front or beside them.</li>



<li>Bring your feet to shoulder-width apart and soften through the knees.</li>



<li>Breathing in through the nose, begin hinging forward at the hips. While keeping your spine straight, drive your butt back and the crown of your head forward.</li>



<li>Keep your neck and head neutral, or in line with your spine, as you bend forward. Resist the urge to look up or to the side.</li>



<li>Once you hit your endpoint, begin driving the hips forward while contracting your glute muscles.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Return to your starting position.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-bulgarian-split-squat" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Dumbbell Bulgarian Split Squat</a></h3>



