<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Set up a low step height at around 6–8 inches. The height can change depending on your ability level.</li>



<li>Ensure that you’re in a suitable space to step up without any obstruction.</li>



<li>Grasp a suitable pair of dumbells and stand directly in front of the raised surface.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Exhale and bring one leg to the raised surface, planting it in front of you.</li>



<li>Shift your weight onto that foot and drive upwards until you&#8217;re on top of the raised surface.</li>



<li>Pause briefly at the top position. Inhale and lower back to the starting position. Change legs and repeat the same movement pattern.</li>
